Juventus superstar, Cristiano Ronaldo has reacted to his side’s Serie A 4-0 victory over Cagliari on Monday. A hat-trick from Ronaldo and a strike from Gonzalo Higuain ensured Maurizio Sarri’s men defeated the visitors at home. Ronaldo scored his 36th league hat-trick against Cagliari. Reacting to the victory, Ronaldo took to his official Twitter page and wrote: “Amazing feeling to kick off 2020 with a hat-trick and a victory!#finoallafine #forzajuve.” The victory over Cagliari means Juventus are now on top of the Serie A table with 45 points from 18 matches. Ronaldo will now hope to lead Juve to victory when they take on AS Roma in their next Serie A fixture on January 12.